      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candle gutters in the draft, much like my very soul. Everything is cold now... the betrayal, the silence of this house, the weight of a heart that no longer knows how to beat for anything but sorrow. It feels as though the shadows are reaching for me, inviting me to simply... cease. To drift into the dark where the pain cannot follow. Does it not seem more merciful to just let the night take everything?",
